      "content": "it sounds like u are saying the deterrence argument is basically just a theory that doesn't hold up to real evidence. if the \"deterrence effect\" is so weak and mostly just hurts people, isn't it more accurate to say that tough on crime policies are inherently flawed or even counterproductive rather than just \"debated\"?",
